Com Hem Said to Pay Up to 475 Basis-Point Spread for Euro Loan

-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 
2011-09-05T16:32:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/com-hem-said-to-pay-up-to-475-basis-point-spread-for-euro-loan.html
Com Hem AB, a Swedish cable company,
plans to pay interest of between 425 basis points and 475 basis
points more than the euro interbank offered rate for a portion
of a loan it’s getting, said a person with knowledge of the
deal.  The company will pay the interest margin on a new, euro-
denominated tranche of a 7.1 billion-kronor ($1.1 billion)
financing to back its buyout by  BC Partners  Ltd., said the
person, who declined to be identified because the transaction’s
private.  The loan in the common currency may be for at least 300
million euros ($423 million), the person said.  BC Partners said July 21 it agreed to buy Com Hem from U.S.
buyout firms  Carlyle Group  and  Providence Equity Partners .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
